message: Checkerboard continues to publish inaccurate information. Sources that are cited have nothing to do with the claim. It does not back it up. Careful please.

Careful here Chekerboard. Original rules were created by Mirl "Red" McCarthy. This is supported by Samuel Jacks, NORDA, SDMRO.,Ringette Canada.Also, read down a couple of paragraphs on this page to see it confirmed again. A good source for this information is a book written by Ken Collins   Collins, Kenneth S. (2004). The Ring Starts Here: An Illustrated History of Ringette. Cobalt, Ontario: Highway Book Shop. . ISBN 0-88954-438-7Try to get a copy to help you fill in the blanks . .

Undid revision 1112204979 by [[Special:Contributions/CheckersBoard|CheckersBoard]] ([[User talk:CheckersBoard|talk]]) Again, this author continues to disrespect Jacks and McCarthy posting inaccurate information. We suggest that Checkersboard read a copy of the only book published on Ringette to help with their understanding of what actually transpired in the early years. We could help in procuring a copy.

CheckersBoard continues to misuse the facts and twist  the story in favour of Jacks. This has been going on for years. Jacks and McCarthy would not be impressed in what you are doing. This posting is another good sample. Calling McCarthy a co-founder and Jacks the inventor. They are both co-founders and both co-inventor. Bye the way, Jacks wanted NORDA credited as being inventor of sport but this citation has been removed over the years.
This user continuously removes citations that have been sourced and makes claims that cannot be sourced properly.
Claims are not substantiated and not a balanced view of what actually occurred. Credit must go to the two founders.
